events.description:
Use this Google Map link to help find the building. Don't use Meetups link! There will be a sign on the door.

If you attended February's meetup can you please spend 30secs and answer this survey? It will help us in organising future events for you all :)

This month we're having a talk on Android security with Jahmel Harris to find out what we can do to make our apps more secure. 

Our second talk is Compiler Reordering by Francis Stephens where we'll find out how the compiler might trip you up when optimising your code.

If you'd like to do a talk or know someone you'd like us to get for a talk then please get in touch! 

Schedule is as follows:

6.00pm - Arrive, mingle, get drinks

6.15pm - Intro

6.20pm - Security & Android - Jahmel Harris

7.10pm - Compiler Reordering - Francis Stephens

7.50pm - Wrap up

8.00pm - The end


Talks

Compiler Reordering - Francis Stephens

There are many things that can ruin your day when writing concurrent software. Many of them are complex, esoteric and dip deep into the details of hardware. But, the biggest danger and often left unmentioned is your compiler.

By exploring very simple source code rewriting we will explore a few things that your compiler can, and often will do.

The talk is intended to give some explanation for the often bizarre and nonsensical rules programming languages provide for concurrent programming.

events.name: GDG Leeds - April 2018
events.description:
GDG Leeds is back!

This month we have Douglass Sillars, author of High Performance Android Apps (http://bit.ly/HighPerfAndroidApps) coming to do his talk "It's Time To Stop Stalling: Mobile App and Video Performance". Doug's focus over the last few years has been the network performance - fast delivery of content.

Here's a little about the talk:

Over 90% of mobile apps utilize network connections to download content. However, many apps have not fully optimized the transfer, causing delays and frustrating customers. In this talk, we'll look at how to profile the network transfers made in your mobile app or website, and walk through a number of best practices to identify and resolve. After this talk, you will know how to test for network inefficiencies, identify some common issues, and be able to resolve them in your code.

Schedule

6.00 - Meet, get drinks
6.10 - "It's Time To Stop Stalling: Mobile App and Video Performance" by Douglas Dollars
7.00 - Fin

events.description:
Join us for 2019's AItechnorth Extended Leeds!

We are delighted to be hosting speakers on this event from the AItechNorth conference 2019 who will be talking about the topics covered on AItechnorth 2019, alongside food, drinks and time to socialize with local developers, designers and more.

All are welcome, the event showcases the latest in ML and AI technologies and more, so is open to anyone with an interest!

The event will start at 5:30 pm, and should finish by 8:00 pm.

We're looking forward to seeing you there!

Update : Unfortunately Dr Firat Tekiner will not be joining but we are delighted to host Ammar Hussain from Google to talk about an AI and ML Solution.

Agenda

17:30 - 18.00 Networking

18.00 - 18.20 Sherin Mathew - AI Tech North - The AI Journey

18.25 - 19.10 Aamar Hussain - Google's Contact Centre solution utilising Google AI and ML(NLP)

19.15 - 20.00 George Kortsaridis - Integrating ML in mobile development

events.name: GDG Leeds - All about Security!
events.description:
October is cyber security awareness month. We are delighted to be hosting talks regarding security on various platforms.
The event will start at 17:30 and should finish by about 20:30 pm.

The agenda for the day:
17.30 - 18.00 Networking
18.00 - 18.45 Aamar Hussain - Unifying User, Device, and App Management with Cloud Identity
18.50 - 19.35 Anastasios Gkouletsos - Building Castle Walls, But Everyone Has A Key
19.40 - 20.15 George Kortsaridis - Hiding Sensitive info in plain sight
20.15 - 20.30 Networking Over Pizza !!

We're looking forward to seeing you there!

More about our speakers:
* Aamar Hussain - Technology Strategists @Google
Unifying User, Device, and App Management with Cloud Identity
A Talk on Google's identity management system the foundation of security managing millions of id's devices and applications. Think of Google mail and the MFA authentication you are using today…

* Anastasios Gkouletsos - Information Security Engineer @Anaplan
Building Castle Walls, But Everyone Has A Key
October is cyber security awareness month.A discussion around security best practices and social engineering

* George Kortsaridis - Android developer @Jet2.com & Jet2holidays
Hiding sensitive info in plain sight
An android application usually holds sensitive information, like names, tokens and even sometimes bank data that we would NOT like to fall into the wrong hands. These days applications can be reverse engineered, and reveal a great chunk of their code. In this session, we will find out exactly which parts of our code can be hacked, and we will also look at ways of securing our data.... in plain sight!

upcoming.name: Cloud Study Jam
upcoming.description:
Join a community of like-minded developers and explore the latest Google Cloud technologies as a team.
Join us for our upcoming Cloud Study Jam and get hands-on experience with Google Cloud Platform delivered by our Google Cloud Authorized Trainer Nabil Hadj-Ahmed.
After the Study Jam, you’ll receive 30-days free access to the entire Qwiklabs catalogue, so you can keep developing your skills at home. Complete all of the labs in the session’s quest, and you’ll earn an additional free month of access to Qwiklabs as well as a badge for your online profile.

Bring a laptop and charger (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed. Don’t forget your charger !!

Agenda:

5.30 pm Welcome and Networking
6:00 pm Introduction to Google Cloud
6:45 pm A Tour of Qwiklabs and the Google Cloud Platform
7:00 pm Lab 1: Creating a Virtual Machine
7:40 pm Lab 2: Getting Started with Cloud Shell & gcloud
8:10 pm Break & Networking
8:30 pm Lab 3: Kubernetes Engine: Qwik Start
9:00 pm Pizza Time !!
